<dl id="n30160c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n30" href="#n30160c">N30 (VI.B.22)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n30all.htm#n30160c"> 160(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> I hypnot</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When in the course of time the curious condition of artificially induced sleep was discovered amid the chaos of the charlatanism of Mesmer, and a new name was required, James Braid, a Scottish surgeon in India, in 1843 coined for this state of artificial sleep the word &ldquo;<mark>hypnotism</mark>&rdquo; from the ordinary Greek word for sleep, &ldquo;hupnos&rdquo;. <small> D. F. Fraser-Harris, <a name="FHMS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FHMS"><cite title="source">Morpheus, or: The Future of Sleep</cite></a> (1928) 12</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c13238m" href="c13all.htm#c13238m">VI.C.13:238(m)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
